.TH "drm_of_find_panel_or_bridge" 9 "drm_of_find_panel_or_bridge" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_of_find_panel_or_bridge \- return connected panel or bridge device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_of_find_panel_or_bridge
.BI "(const struct device_node *np "  ","
.BI "int port "  ","
.BI "int endpoint "  ","
.BI "struct drm_panel **panel "  ","
.BI "struct drm_bridge **bridge "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "np" 12
device tree node containing encoder output ports
.IP "port" 12
port in the device tree node
.IP "endpoint" 12
endpoint in the device tree node
.IP "panel" 12
pointer to hold returned drm_panel
.IP "bridge" 12
pointer to hold returned drm_bridge
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Given a DT node's port and endpoint number, find the connected node and
return either the associated struct drm_panel or drm_bridge device. Either
\fIpanel\fP or \fIbridge\fP must not be NULL.

Returns zero if successful, or one of the standard error codes if it fails.
